sections.title: Introduction
sections.content:
Related articles

- Language Server Protocol

This page attempts to list all programming languages with a compiler / interpreter packaged for Arch Linux.

- Assembly – as of binutils, fasm, nasm, yasm
- Ada – Ada
- AWK
- Ballerina - ballerinaAUR
- BASIC – freebasic AOZ Studio Gambas QB64 – qb64AUR
- C – GCC, Clang C++ – GCC, Clang Objective-C – GCC, Clang
- C# – Mono, .NET Core
- Crystal
- D
- Dart – dart
- Erlang – erlang Elixir
- Factor – factorAUR
- Forth – 4thAUR, gforthAUR, retroforthAUR
- Fortran – GCC
- Go – go, GCC
- Java Groovy – groovy
- GDL - gnudatalanguageAUR
- Haskell
- JavaScript – rhino, v8AUR[broken link: package not found], quickjsAUR Node.js
- Julia
- Kotlin – kotlin
- Lisp dialects Clojure Common Lisp Emacs Lisp Scheme racket - racket, racket-minimal newLISP – newlispAUR PicoLisp – picolispAUR
- Lua – lua, luajit
- ML Standard ML – smlnj, mlton, polyml, mosmlAUR, smlsharpAUR OCaml – ocaml
- Nim – nim
- Octave
